===Noun===
'''polygraph'''
# a device which measures and records several physiological variables such as blood pressure, heart rate, respiration and skin conductivity while a series of questions is being asked, in an attempt to detect lies.

A polygraph is a device which measures heart rate, blood pressure, and perspiration while a series of questions are being asked im attept to detect lies. There is no scientific proof that this lie detector will detect all lies; only 90% get caught.